<title type="html"><![CDATA[ContentEditable is support in Internet Explorer 5.5+]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=15&amp;p=130#p130"><![CDATA[
I tested contentEditable support in Internet Explorer.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Tool:</span><br /><ul>Install multiple versions of IE on your PC<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://tredosoft.com/Multiple_IE">http://tredosoft.com/Multiple_IE</a><!-- m --></ul><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">HTML test file:</span><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;html&gt;<br />&lt;body&gt;<br /><br />&lt;p contenteditable=&quot;true&quot;&gt;This is a sample paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;<br /><br />&lt;/body&gt;<br />&lt;/html&gt;<br /></code></dd></dl><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Process:</span><br />I opened the test file in each version of IE (3.0, 4.01, 5.01, 5.5) until I found the version that did something with the paragraph (version 5.5).<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Results:</span><br />In Internet Explorer 5.5(and higher) you can type in the paragraph. It seems contentEditable works.<br /><br />Acually putting &quot;contentEditable&quot; to work as a tool, ex. a web-based word processor, is a programing problem/challenge not an issue with the spec.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=59">wgabrie</a> — Wed Apr 18, 2007 5:57 pm</p><hr />
